parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure in Wet Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system in wet conditions can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The power steering system fails or becomes difficult to maneuver when driving through puddles of water or in rainy conditions
making it hard to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wheel lockup can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to maneuver or locks up
making it hard to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ball joint breaks or fails
causing the vehicle to lose control or crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the key can be removed from the ignition switch while the vehicle is in motion
the vehicle fails to start
the ignition switch fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, including the airbag system, anti-lock braking system, and suspension system, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of power
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
the airbag system fails to operate
the anti-lock braking system fails to operate
the suspension system fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to become stuck in the down position, increasing the risk of theft or injury.
symptoms: The window becomes stuck in the down position
the window regulator fails to operate properly
the window motor continues to run even when the window is stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated steering wheel can cause burns or injuries to the driver.
symptoms: The heated steering wheel overheats
smoke comes from the heated steering wheel
the heated steering wheel fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants may not be adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
airbag warning light illuminates
seatbelts fail to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
airbag service light illuminates
check airbag warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and electrical system can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Ignition turns off
vehicle loses power
steering and brakes fail to operate properly
engine dies.
